      • generateValues

        protected boolean generateValues​(int row,
                                 int col)
        Fill the values array with unique digits such that each row and column in the array contains all integers from 1 to this.size. This is done recursively and slowly, but hey, it works. It's fine for grids under size 30. Over 30 it shits itself, not sure why. It might be recursion levels, or maybe I'm just not waiting long enough. Although to be fair, I'm not sure size 30 KenKen puzzles are even solvable by humans.
        Parameters:
        row - Row to fill.
        col - Column to fill.
        Returns:
        Will return true if all tiles are valid. Since it's recursive, if the top level returns false, something went wrong.

        protected boolean generateRegionsRecursive()
        Go through the grid, expanding each region by 1 tile. Repeat until no tiles remain.
        Parameters:

        col - y-coordinate to generate
        num - region num (value in this.regions array)
        Returns:
        true if generation is completed.
